free_txt: English translation
The spectrometer used six silicon dE-E
telescopes. The E detector was 1.1 mm thick, and
dE-detector' active thickness was 12-17 mu-m.
Measurements were also made with two telescopes.
The systematic error was due to the errors in
target thickness and deuteron flux
Error in target thickness
Error in deuteron flux
LiF targets deposited on aluminum 0.55 mu-m thick
backings (targets: 173 mu-g/cm**(2) 91.06% Li-6 and
165 mu-g/cm**(2) 95.22% Li-7), 0.3 mu-m thick carbon
backings (target: 236 mu-g/cm**(2) 91.06% Li-6) and
on a poly-n-xylylene (C8H6) backing 0.8 mu-m thick
(target: 176 mu-g/cm**(2) 91.06% Li-6). The targets
were positioned at an angle of 45 degrees to the ion
beam direction.
Entry was approved by Dr. L.N. Generalov
Random errors were obtained by averaging
the results from different series of measurements
with different targets to reflect explicit random
errors in the values that determine the differential
cross-sections along with implicit errors in setting
angles, unevenness in the thickness of targets, and
other factors.
